These modifications allow a user to create custom regions in Python. They just need to add the module to the network and then they can create their custom region. Additionally, I updated network_api_demo to show how to use a custom region.

Fixes #2057

@scottpurdy - please review

`socket.gethostbyname_ex('poppy')` will always return 127.0.0.1, but `socket.gethostbyname_ex('poppy.local')` will return the local IPv4 (10.x.x.x or 192.168.x.x).

This solve the IP resolution when there is no network access, and for some network configuration such as issue #169 

